{
  "text": "VEGF concentration in follicular\u00afuid is said to be dependent on the quality and number of granulosa cells responding [CITATION_1] . In both groups we observed a negative correlation between follicular\u00afuid VEGF and granulosa cell number which was independent of follicle size. Greater granulosa cell numbers have been associated with more competent follicles [CITATION_2] and lower follicular\u00afuid VEGF levels with more oocytes [CITATION_3] and better embryo quality [CITATION_4] . The fact that this correlation was more signi\u00aecant in the coasted group may be due to the differential effect of gonadotrophin withdrawal on individual follicles in favour of those follicles with greater numbers of granulosa cells/most competent.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "16565398",
    "[CITATION_2]": "2789337",
